          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρομαι</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρεαι</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρωμαι, -ηαι, -ηται,
            -ώμεθα</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρεο,
            εἰρέσθω</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρεσθαι</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰρόμενος</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρετο, -οντο</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰρήσομαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ask, inquire</span>, often <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινά τι</span>, also <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφί
            τινι, περί τινος</span>, etc.; and w. acc. of thing inquired
          about or for, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φυλακᾶς δ᾽ ἃ̄ς εἴρεαι,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 10.416</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Ζ
            239</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
          11.542</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
